*libarchive-1.2.38 (18 Feb 2006)

  18 Feb 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +libarchive-1.2.38.ebuild:
  Bump following upstream.

  05 Jan 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  -libarchive-1.02.036.ebuild:
  Drop old version.

  30 Dec 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  libarchive-1.2.37.ebuild:
  Replace userland_Darwin check with a CHOST check before moving in /lib.

  08 Nov 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  libarchive-1.2.37.ebuild:
  036 shouldn't have been stable. Make sure 37 it's not.

*libarchive-1.2.37 (08 Nov 2005)

  08 Nov 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +libarchive-1.2.37.ebuild:
  Updated to latest upstream version. OSX patch shouldn't be needed anymore.
  Changed versioning scheme by upstream.

  05 Nov 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  -files/libarchive-1.02.027-libtool.patch, -libarchive-1.02.027-r1.ebuild,
  -libarchive-1.02.030.ebuild, -libarchive-1.02.034.ebuild:
  Remove old versions.

*libarchive-1.02.036 (13 Oct 2005)

  13 Oct 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +libarchive-1.02.036.ebuild:
  Added New version, now the libtool patch is applied by upstream. Note: the
  soname has changed, if you are using this on Gentoo/FreeBSD, recompile
  bsdtar with +static before installing this.

  09 Oct 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  libarchive-1.02.030.ebuild, libarchive-1.02.034.ebuild:
  No need to touch the GNU files as now eautoreconf recognize when using
  --foreign.

*libarchive-1.02.034 (25 Sep 2005)

