*libarchive-1.02.032 (07 Sep 2005)

  07 Sep 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  -libarchive-1.02.031.ebuild, +libarchive-1.02.032.ebuild:
  Updated libarchive with new upstream version. Fixes the problem I had to
  patch in bsdtar yesterday.

*libarchive-1.02.031 (06 Sep 2005)

  06 Sep 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +libarchive-1.02.031.ebuild:
  New libarchive upstream.

  05 Sep 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  libarchive-1.02.030.ebuild:
  Added elibtoolize to fix links on Gentoo/FreeBSD.

  30 Aug 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  libarchive-1.02.030.ebuild:
  Use eautoreconf, so that it returns to work on OSX. Don't mangle .so
  libraries on Darwin.

*libarchive-1.02.030 (28 Aug 2005)

  28 Aug 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +libarchive-1.02.030.ebuild:
  Updated to latest upstream version. Dropped osx patch as it's fixed upstream
  now.

*libarchive-1.02.027-r1 (13 Aug 2005)

  13 Aug 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +files/libarchive-1.02.027-libtool.patch, +libarchive-1.02.027-r1.ebuild:
  Use libtoolize to build libarchive, to have the shared version.

  28 Jul 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  libarchive-1.02.027.ebuild:
  Stable on amd64.

  22 Jul 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +files/libarchive-1.02.027-osx.patch, libarchive-1.02.027.ebuild:
  Added patch for OSX compatibility.

  16 Jun 2005; David Holm <dholm@gentoo.org> libarchive-1.02.027.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc.

*libarchive-1.02.027 (16 Jun 2005)

  16 Jun 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml,
  +libarchive-1.02.027.ebuild:
  First revision. libarchive is needed by bsdtar which is its primary interface.

